This article is a notice from the White House announcing the continuation of the national emergency with respect to certain terrorist attacks. The national emergency was initially declared on September 14, 2001, following the terrorist attacks on September 11, 2001. The President is continuing the national emergency for another year due to the ongoing terrorist threat and the need to maintain the powers and authorities to deal with it. The notice will be published in the Federal Register and transmitted to Congress. The statement is signed by Barack Obama.